  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for customizing a typeface when cloning it.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` specifies parameters for customizing a typeface when cloning it via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. It allows selecting a font collection index, a color palette, palette color overrides, and a variable-font design position.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = new SKFourByteTag('w','g','h','t'), Value = 700 }
    }
};
using var cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
